  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate, nominal-only validation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model trained to predict CFD hemolysis indices for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Validation evidence covers nominal operating conditions drawn from the same distribution as the training set. A note in the assessment states that real-world distribution shift has been studied separately; no link or reference to that study is provided.",
