    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-surrogate-nominal-accuracy-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal test-set accuracy — ML hemolysis surrogate",
      "description": "The ML surrogate (gradient-boosted ensemble) was evaluated on a held-out test set drawn from the same CFD design-of-experiments campaign used for training (Latin Hypercube, 5 flow-speed combinations, nominal blood viscosity and hematocrit). Mean absolute error in normalised hemolysis index: 2.3%. R² = 0.974 across 120 test cases. Acceptance criterion RH < 1 correctly classified in 98.3% of test cases. No noise injection, no covariate-shift study, and no adversarial perturbation evaluation was performed. The assessment narrative notes that robustness under real-world distribution shift has been studied separately, but no citation, dataset identifier, or report reference is supplied."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-surrogate-cross-validation-002",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "5-fold cross-validation on training distribution",
      "description": "Five-fold cross-validation was performed on the full CFD training corpus (600 cases). Mean R² = 0.969 ± 0.008; RMSE in normalised hemolysis index = 0.031 ± 0.004. All folds drawn from the same nominal operating envelope; no out-of-distribution folds were constructed. Distribution shift, sensor noise, and adversarial inputs were not evaluated in any fold."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-surrogate-comparison-predicate-003",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Comparison against predicate device hemolysis benchmark",
      "description": "Surrogate predictions for the 5 worst-case operating points identified by the model were compared against experimental hemolysis measurements from the predicate device. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 for all 5 points. Comparison conducted under nominal inlet conditions (steady flow, standard hematocrit 40%, temperature 37 °C). No perturbation of inlet boundary conditions or material property uncertainty was explored."
    }
  ],
